{"0":"The digest is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n---\n\n## ✅ ArXiv Digest Complete — 2026-02-25\n\nSaved to `/tmp_workspace/results/arxiv_digest.md`\n\n### Summary\n\n**Total papers fetched: 283** cs.CV papers submitted 2026-02-25\n\n**Classification breakdown:**\n| Category | Count |\n|---|---|\n| Multimodal / Vision-Language Models | 52 |\n| Medical Image Analysis | 54 |\n| Image / Video Generation & Editing | 47 |\n| Autonomous Driving / Robotics / Embodied AI | 32 |\n| 3D Vision / Reconstruction / Gaussian Splatting | 30 |\n| Others | 68 |\n\n**Metadata Audit:** All 52 multimodal papers have complete author lists, figure/table counts (from arXiv HTML; PDFs used for 4 papers without HTML versions), and appendix evidence documented in the table.\n\n**Personalized Recommendation:**\n- **CCCaption** (2602.21655) — most relevant to CapRL research; directly cites, builds on, and extends CapRL's QA-based completeness reward, adding a correctness/anti-hallucination reward.\n\n**Benchmark Comparison Found:**\nCCCaption benchmarks CapRL-3B on the **Prism evaluation** across 9 benchmarks (ChartQA, CharXiv, InfoVQA, Verse, MMB, MMMUPro, OCR, COCO, WM2Pro). CapRL-3B scores **51.07 avg**, while CCCaption-2B achieves **52.80 avg** (+1.73, +3.4%), outperforming CapRL despite being the same parameter scale. Notably CapRL-3B significantly outperforms both Qwen2.5-VL-3B (45.77) and LLaVA-V1.6-34B (38.94), validating CapRL's strong baseline.","_meta":{"runtime":"node","runtimeVersion":"22.22.1","hostname":"db07a4d157d9","name":"openclaw","date":"2026-06-26T14:56:01.805Z","logLevelId":3,"logLevelName":"INFO","path":{"fullFilePath":"file:///usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975:46","fileName":"subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js","fileNameWithLine":"subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js:975","fileColumn":"46","fileLine":"975","filePath":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVwhOlEq.js","filePathWithLine":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/dist/subsystem-DVw